body:
**Description**

I am using a SkiaSharp library for measuring the text and I have recently upgraded the SkiaSharp library version [2.80.0]. Then exception occurs while measuring the Unicode text and this exception are not comes from the older version [1.59.3].
kindly provide your suggestion to resolve this issue.

**Code**
```
string text1 = "\ud83c";
                string text2 = "\ud835";
                float fontsize = 12;
                float skiaMeasurement = 0;
                using (SKPaint paint = new SKPaint())
                    {
                        paint.Typeface = SKTypeface.FromFamilyName("Arial");
                        paint.Color = SKColors.Black;
                        paint.IsAntialias = true;   
                        paint.TextSize = fontsize;
                        paint.SubpixelText = true;
                        paint.TextAlign = SKTextAlign.Left;
                        paint.TextEncoding = SKTextEncoding.Utf8;
                        SKRect rect = new SKRect();
                        skiaMeasurement = paint.MeasureText(text2, ref rect);
                        Console.WriteLine("SKia Width = " + skiaMeasurement);
                    }
```
<!-- a snippet of code that demonstrates the issue -->

**Expected Behavior**

SKia Width = 9

**Actual Behavior**

Exception occurs.

**Basic Information**

- Version with issue:  2.80.0
- Last known good version:  1.59.3
- IDE:  Visual Studio 2017
- Platform Target Frameworks: .NET Core 2.1
  

